      • setMaxQueueSize

        public void setMaxQueueSize(int maxQueueSize)
        Sets the the maximum size of a queue to buffer metrics for asynchronous publishing.

        On every LocalMetricsServiceFactory.setRefreshInterval(long) tick a new entry with the snapshot of current metrics is added to the queue of this size. If there is no more space in the queue (f.e. due to slow network connection between the publisher and InfluxDB) then such entries will be dropped and will not be published to InfluxDB.

        Value of this parameter must be above zero. Default value is 100.

        Parameters:
        maxQueueSize - Maximum queue size.
